import math
import sys
import itertools
import fractions
wtf = sys.stdin.read()
wtf = wtf.strip().split('\n')
GAP = 3
for t in [wtf[i:i + GAP] for i in range(1, len(wtf), GAP)]:
    n = int(t[0])
    R = list(map(int, [x for x in t[1]]))
    B = list(map(int, [x for x in t[2]]))
    Rm = 0
    Bm = 0
    for p in zip(R, B):
        if p[0] > p[1]:
            Rm += 1
        elif p[0] < p[1]:
            Bm += 1
    if Rm > Bm:
        print('RED')
    elif Rm < Bm:
        print('BLUE')
    else:
        print('EQUAL')
